# All scripts should begin with a shebang, which defines the path to the interpreter.

# All scripts should include comments to describe their use.

Pattern Matching:
-----------------

  * -> matches any string, including null
  ? -> matches any single character
  [character class] -> matches any one of the characters enclosed between [ and ].
  [^...] -> matches the complement (any character not in the class)
  [a-z] -> matches the range of characters from a to z
  [[:class;]] -> matches according to these POSIX classes: alnum, alpha, ascii, blank, cntrl, digit, graph, lower, punct, space
